File: An Emirates Airbus A380-842 aircraft. AFP/Karim Sahib JOHANNESBURG - United Arab Emirates based airline Emirates says its flights from South Africa will remain suspended until 20 March. But in a notice on its website, the airline says flights to Johannesburg will resume from Thursday. Outbound passenger flights will remain suspended. READ: Emirates temporarily suspends flights to SA Virgin Atlantic has also extended its ban on flights to and from South Africa and may not resume them until April. British Airways has suspended all South Africa international flights until the middle of next month. READ: Qatar Airways increases SA flights The only Middle Eastern airline that has continued flying to and from South Africa since October is Qatar Airways. The Doha-based carrier has since upped its flight frequency to South Africa, despite Qatar being off-limits to international travellers.